General Lee gave David Miri a more than decent ride in the Junju Handicap shelving favourite, Unforgettable, for Mary Binks and Stewart McCann.Peter Kinuthia and Onesmus Mutua were back in business with a tidy double. Establishing himself once again as one of Kenya's finest, Silverstone Air (James Muhindi), made light work of the Mzee Wa Pwani Trophy for Captain Somow.
Silverstone Air is all quality. Just push a button and boom - off he goes.
Western Ballad was not quite her usual brimming self, being thwarted for second place by Pharoah's Advocate. Gold Pot was unable to navigate the tricky bend, supporting his love for only sprinting in future. He was not even roaming in the neighbourhood.



