So, who was missing from Ngong? None other than our Champion jockey, Lesley Sercombe, under the miserable spell of flu - nothing to do with Covid-19.  
The Ganze Maiden was maybe a low-key event for some, but not for young 20-year-old, Tony Kuria, winning his first race as a trainer, and, part-owner. How stirring is that? Well done Tony. Keep it rocking.



