General Lee gave David Miri a more than decent ride in the Junju Handicap shelving favourite, Unforgettable, for Mary Binks and Stewart McCann.
As previously stated, Algy is a very good horse, but has issues with starting. Yesterday no such obstacles. He almost caught Firing Line in the Alpa Romeo Trophy- a short-head judgement is encouraging for Oliver Gray. Lady Eccles was happy to be competing down the straight, forging a laudable third.
Peter Kinuthia and Onesmus Mutua were back in business with a tidy double.





